sentences: Eakes was originally Miss Georgia in 1983.
The band signed to Epic Records in 1987, and recorded their first single - a Giorgio Moroder and Tom Whitlock track titled "All I Need Is You".
The song was included on the official soundtrack release, which was released during the same year.
The band then recorded their self-titled album Big Trouble which was released in 1988.
Today, the album, although on CD and vinyl, has remained out-of-print.
Big Trouble had one chart entry in the U.S., the single "Crazy World", released in 1987.
A second single followed in 1988, the Moroder-Whitlock song "When the Love Is Good", which was also taken from the self-titled album, and featured the non-album b-side "Last Kiss".
The band's final release was the 1988 CD maxi-single "Crazy World", released in the UK only, which was backed by the two album tracks "Say Yes" and "Trains and Boats and Planes".
Following the band's split, Eakes, previously an actress, would win the role of Macy Alexander on the soap opera The Bold and the Beautiful, which she played from 1989 to 2000.

She returned to music in 1994 with a duet album with Jeff Tracta, titled Bold and Beautiful Duets, which went double-platinum in Europe.
Another collaboration with Tracta followed in 1998, with the album Glamour Duets II.
Two solo albums followed, the 1998 album Here and Now, as well as the 2005 album Something Beautiful.
